Western Cape ANC secretary Faiez Jacobs allegedly assaulted a party staffer at the its offices last November. CAPE TOWN - The assault case against the African National Congress (ANC)'s Western Cape secretary Faiez Jacobs has been postponed until next year.Jacobs made a brief appearance in the Cape Town Magistrates Court on Wednesday where he faces assault charges.He allegedly assaulted an ANC staffer at the party s offices last November.Jacobs will return to the Cape Town Magistrates Court in February.He will be asked to plea to charges of assault with the intent to cause grievous bodily harm.Jacobs was charged earlier this year after he allegedly attacked former ANC researcher Wesley Seale for refusing to draw up a report.The provincial secretary was found guilty by the ANC's disciplinary committee.An 18-month suspension handed down to him was set aside for five years.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)